<TEXT>
seventy dog teams and mushers were set 
to start the last great race on earth on saturday the grueling 
1100milelong iditarod trail sled dog race from anchorage to nome 
teams were expected to encounter some of the harshest weather in 
the races 18year history said race manager jack niggemyer 
subzero temperatures accompanied by strong winds the heaviest 
snowfall in a quartercentury ash from redoubt volcano and 
starving aggressive moose have combined to make it a tough year to 
race and a tough year to train he said 
awful weather niggemyer said its probably snowed 40 
inches in the last two days 
the race usually lasts from 11 to 18 days the record time set 
by susan butcher of manley alaska in 1987 is 11 days two hours 
and five minutes butcher won the race in 1986 1987 and 1988 
some participants and race observers said they expect this 
years race to be slow going because of the deep snow and 
poorlypacked trail 
we might run out of trail said lavon barve a musher from 
wasilla alaska its up to the mushers to snowshoe or 
whatever he said it will be barves ninth race he finished 
fifth last year 
the iditarod began in 1973 it commemorates the 1925 emergency 
delivery of diphtheria serum to nome on the bering sea the serum 
taken overland by sled dog because airplanes couldnt get through 
was credited with saving hundreds of lives in the remote coastal 
town 
the trail begins in anchorage and heads northwest across the 
giant alaska range and onto the treeless tundra eventually it 
winds along the yukon river to the bering sea 
since 1973 the iditarod has grown in fame and stature this 
year mushers have come from as far as france and switzerland 
companies spend tens of thousands of dollars to sponsor top 
competitors 
rick swenson of two rivers alaska the only person to win the 
iditarod four times will be trying for a fifth win butcher will 
attempt to equal swensons fourtime win record 
</TEXT>
