<TEXT>
carol guzy of the washington post was named 
newspaper photographer of the year friday with magnums eugene 
richards winning the top magazine award in the 47th annual pictures 
of the year competition 
the winners were announced by the university of missouri school 
of journalism which cosponsored the 47th annual pictures of the 
year competition with the national press photographers association 
the entries were judged last month at columbia by a 12member 
panel the competition is supported by grants from canon usa inc 
and the professional photography division of eastman kodak co 
following is a list of the top three winners in each category 
