rock singer billy idol who suffered a broken 
leg and forearm in a motorcycle accident last month has been 
released from the hospital 
idol 34 was released friday from cedarssinai medical center 
and will require a period of rehabilitation hospital spokesman ron 
wise said 
the spikehaired singer suffered a compound fracture of his 
right leg between the knee and ankle and a broken left forearm on 
feb 6 he underwent several operations on his leg 
police said idol ran a stop sign and hit a car while riding home 
from a hollywood studio where he had just completed work on the 
album charmed life which is scheduled for release april 17 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
comedian bob newhart says he had fun making 
newhart for the last eight years but this year is the last for 
the cbs situation comedy 
newhart in which the comedian stars as an embattled 
hotelier will have its last broadcast in april the 60yearold 
newhart said that another year for the sitcom was scuttled by 
demands made by mtm the shows producers he and cbs are in talks 
to develop a new situation comedy 
our series was the perfect example of how much fun episodic 
television can be newhart said 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
soviet parliamentarian boris yeltsin 
kicks off an international tour here next week to promote his book 
against the grain yeltsin arrives in stockholm on monday the 
worldwide publishing date for the book which promises rare insight 
into the political games behind the kremlin walls said inger 
sjoholmlarsson spokeswoman of publisher forum ab 
sjoholmlarsson said a first swedish edition of 15000 to 18000 
copies was being printed 
yeltsin 58 is a member of the congress of peoples deputies 
and a deputy in the supreme soviet legislature 
excerpts of against the grain have appeared in swedish 
papers they described the privileged lives of the soviet political 
elite and criticized soviet leader mikhail gorbachev for moving 
too slowly in reforming soviet society 
yeltsin will tour norway west germany italy france the 
netherlands great britain and the united states 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
psychiatric social worker sophie freud 
granddaughter of sigmund freud the founder of psychoanalysis says 
shes never undergone psychoanalysis and doesnt plan to 
im just the kind of addictive person who would get lost in 
some kind of dependency relationship in analysis she told about 
200 people friday at the university of pittsburgh its too 
dangerous to my psychic makeup 
ms freud 65 is a professor of social work at simmons college 
in boston and a noted therapist 
she poked fun at some of her grandfathers ideas saying for 
example that she doesnt agree with his contention that only men 
are capable of true passion 
women love only themselves with an intensity comparable to 
mans love for them her grandfather wrote in 1914 nor does 
their need lie in the direction of loving but of being loved and 
that man finds favor with them who fulfills this condition 
thats ridiculous ms freud said 
sometimes i question whether men are capable of love she 
joked before the predominantly female audience 
</TEXT>
