<TEXT>
a teenager fleeing cuba crossed most of 
the hazardous florida straits on a windsurfer that an east german 
tourist had given him a coast guard spokesman said 
lester moreno perez 17 was in good health after being picked 
up by a bahamian freighter about 30 miles south of key west petty 
officer james wentworth said friday 
the youth had begun the trip from cuba 16 hours earlier on 
thursday and had sailed about 60 miles on the windsurfer before it 
broke wentworth said 
it wasnt a cheap windsurfer he said it was a nice one 
it wasnt homemade 
moreno perez told coast guard officers he was given the 
austrianmade threemeter long surfboard by an east german tourist 
who wanted him to have his freedom said petty officer richard 
rodriguez 
the wishbone boom which the windsurfer holds while sailing 
broke in the early morning friday forcing moreno perez to rig up a 
makeshift device rodriguez said 
moreno perez who told officials he has family in miami was 
being questioned friday by the immigration and naturalization 
service 
hundreds of cuban refugees have attempted the dangerous passage 
to the florida keys on homemade rafts rickety boats or innertubes 
many have died along the way 
</TEXT>
