<TEXT>
irreplaceable scientific information from us 
space missions is in danger because of the deplorable 
conditions in which nasa allows hundreds of thousands of magnetic 
tapes to be stored a congressional agency says 
the general accounting office an arm of congress that audits 
the performance of federal agencies said friday that investigators 
found tapes in dusty hallways and in a basement where some had been 
partially submerged by a flood 
the national aeronautics and space administration in a letter 
signed by john e obrien assistant deputy administrator told the 
gao we take strong exception to the implication that nasa is 
not safeguarding the space science data as a national resources for 
future generations 
we believe that the tone of the report is unnecessarily harsh 
and contains sweeping generalizations and extrapolations which we 
believe to be unfounded and unsubstantiated obrien said 
nasa said it had experienced no significant loss of scientific 
data as identified by our science customers it also said its own 
testing has shown a more than satisfactory preservation of data 
the gao in turn rejected nasas criticism and said there was 
reason for concern that data stored on the tapes is at serious 
risk of becoming partially or completely unusable 
the congressional monitors said they had visited 10 tape storage 
and processing facilities and had found that eight failed to comply 
with at least two of the regulations established by the national 
archives and records administration for the handling of magnetic 
tapes 
in a summary of its findings the gao said hundreds of 
thousands of tapes containing space science data are stored under 
deplorable conditions 
five of the facilities lacked adequate temperature and 
humidity control fire protection water protection or tape 
maintenance the congressional agency said 
in some instances gao found tapes stored in hallways 
basements and dusty warehouses not designed for tape storage for 
example in one major facility gao found nearly 300000 tapes 
packed in boxes covered by dust and stacked on shipping pallets 
in one place the agency said it found more than 4000 tapes 
stored in a dirty basement that had been flooded in 1985 
submerging approximately half of some of the tapes and leaving a 
film of debris on them 
the gao said that some of the most significant tape management 
deficiencies were found in the two largest facilities the 
national space science data center at the goddard space flight 
center in greenbelt md which stores more than 113000 magnetic 
tapes and the tape staging and storage facility in landover md 
which stores and tracks more than 860000 tapes 
by contrast the agency said the us geological surveys eros 
data center in sioux falls sd and the digital equipment corps 
data protection services in dominguez hills calif were in full 
or partial compliance with federal standards and industry 
guidelines 
other facilities visited were the national archives los angeles 
federal records center in laguna niguel calif and its washington 
national records center the smithsonian astrophysical observatory 
washington the multimission image processing facility of the jet 
propulsion laboratory and the infrared processing and analysis 
center of the california institute of technology both in pasadena 
calif and the center for astrophysics and space sciences of the 
university of california at san diego in la jolla calif 
