the food and drug administration says the drug 
azt may be recommended for adults infected with the virus that 
causes aids even if the patients dont have symptoms of the disease 
the drug has been used for three years to treat patients 
severely ill with aids and related problems 
the studies and the change in labeling mean that better 
treatment can now be offered to thousands of people at earlier 
stages of infection with the aids virus before their health 
deteriorates critically health and human services secretary 
louis sullivan said in a statement 
fda on friday approved new labels expanding the drugs use after 
two federally sponsored studies showed that azt slowed progress of 
the disease when administered to infected patients with early 
symptoms or none at all 
the national institute of allergy and infectious diseases and 
burroughs wellcome co the drug manufacturer conducted trials 
involving 2000 volunteers azt was shown to slow down the progress 
of aids while causing far fewer severe side effects than those 
suffered by patients in advanced stages of the disease 
the fda move should make it easier for patients to obtain 
reimbursement under their health insurance policies said burroughs 
wellcome vice president jr whitehead 
earlier this year the fda approved a labeling change that cut in 
half the recommended adult dose of azt the change reduced both the 
frequency of side effects and the cost of treatment to patients 
on oct 26 the fda approved the use of azt for children with 
advanced cases of aids the expanded application announced friday 
applies to adults only but an agency spokesman said the question 
of making azt treatment available earlier to hivinfected children 
is expected to come up at an fda advisory meeting later this month 
acquired immune deficiency syndrome is a contagious disease that 
attacks the bodys immune system rendering it incapable of 
resisting other diseases and infections 
as of dec 31 1989 aids had been diagnosed in 117781 
americans of whom 60 percent or 70313 have died since june 1 
1981 
