federal task forces are moving into eight 
cities later this month to try to catch people breaking federal gun 
laws that bring mandatory prison sentences 
the project achilles task forces will be in place by march 26 in 
new york philadelphia los angeles chicago miami detroit 
washington and phoenix the bureau of alcohol tobacco and firearms 
said friday 
the atf conducted a similar fourmonth armed career criminal 
operation in washington last year as a prelude to the upcoming 
project 
congress last year included 45 million in the atfs budget for 
1990 specifically as salaries for 75 fulltime workers in the 
achilles task forces in five cities but the atf expanded that 
number to eight 
the agents will work with state and local law enforcement 
officials 
the task forces will be targeting people under two sections of 
federal law that call for mandatory sentencing 
one says anyone convicted of a felony crime of violence or drug 
charge who is carrying a gun automatically is sentenced for at 
least five years on the weaponpossession charge 
the other section says that a person who has three previous 
felony convictions for a violent crime or drug offense will be 
sentenced to at least 15 years on the firearm charge 
