cuban government which has vehemently protested the transmissions 
are a violation of sovereignty and international broadcasting 
agreements 
besides said ariel ricardo press officer of the cuban 
interests section in washington its no secret to the cuban 
people whats going on in the world cubans are quite well 
informed through the cuban media and other sources such as the 
british broadcasting corp and miami radio stations whose powerful 
signals reach the island 
and ricardo said just because the cuban government has 
tolerated radio marti which it also opposes doesnt mean we 
consider radio marti right 
us broadcasters especially in florida are worried about 
retaliatory broadcasts from cuba or direct interference from tv 
martis signal schoenfeld says tv martis specially designed 
highly directional antenna will virtually eliminate interference to 
domestic broadcasters 
spanishlanguage programs from washington will be relayed to a 
