heal the hurt left by incumbent marion barrys indictment on 
drug and perjury charges 
fauntroy the citys nonvoting delegate to congress since 1971 
said he reached his decision to seek the democratic nomination 
after weeks of painful and tearful consideration 
i just might be able to attract and unleash the unprecedented 
partnership of talented people required to heal the hurt and end 
the polarization in our city fauntroy told a prayer breakfast 
fauntroy 57 was an aide to civil rights leader martin luther 
king jr in the southern christian leadership conference in the 
1960s he is an ordained baptist minister 
in congress he has pushed statehood for the district of 
columbia and is the no2 democrat on the house banking committee 
as a delegate he cannot vote on the floor but may vote in 
committee 
fauntroy joins a crowded field in the democratic primary where 
the political picture was turned into turmoil by barrys drug 
arrest victory in the democratic primary has long been tantamount 
to election in washington 
barry who is being treated for substance abuse at a south 
carolina hospital has not announced his political plans but a 
recent washington post poll show the mayor would still lead a field 
of the other candidates 
barry was arrested jan 18 on a misdemeanor cocaine possession 
charge he was indicted last month on cocaine possession and 
perjury charges in connection with an investigation into his ties 
to a convicted drug dealer 
the justice department has been investigating allegations that 
fauntroy had a noshow employee on his payroll fauntroys 
advisers told potential supporters last week that the justice 
department probe has been scuttled 
but a law enforcement source speaking only on condition of 
anonymity said the probe has not been abandoned 
