amendment legislation is not the answer said a letter to 
senators from jason s berman president of the recording industry 
association of america inc 
as a father of three teenage daughters i believe i not 
recordstore owners or government should be the judge of what is 
suitable music for the home if i am not concerned with my 
childrens wellbeing no label will make a difference 
tanya blackwood of the association said the burden of the law 
will fall on recordstore owners 
it will make the retailer doublecheck everything that comes 
in the store and will force him to err on the conservative side 
