the newspapers mention of a posthostage era was the latest 
in a series of recent indications from iran and allied shiite 
moslem militants in lebanon that western captives held in lebanon 
could be released 
there are 18 westerners missing in lebanon most of whom are 
believed held by proiranian factions they are eight americans 
four britons two west germans two swiss an irishman and an 
italian 
