the junior partner in west german chancellor 
helmut kohls coalition government joined poland on saturday in 
attacking kohl for his latest position on the eastern border of a 
united germany 
one member of the junior party was quoted as saying the 
government could break up over the issue if kohl persists in his 
stand 
meanwhile former west german chancellor willy brandt returned 
to east germany to do more campaigning for east german candidates 
in the march elections 
the soviet news agency tass announced in moscow that east german 
premier hans modrow will pay a working visit to moscow on 
monday and tuesday no other details were immediately available 
kohl on friday offered poland a treaty fixing its border with 
east germany but he said poland should also confirm its 1953 
decision to renounce any world war ii reparations he said poland 
should also ensure protection of the rights of ethnic germans in 
poland 
poland has pushed for the treaty to prevent a reunited germany 
from pressing claims to polish territory that was part of prewar 
germany polish officials angrily rejected kohls new proposal 
on saturday kohls own government partner the free democrat 
party added its voice to the criticism 
foreign minister hansdietrich genscher was quoted by the 
luebecker nachrichten newspaper as saying the party and kohls 
christian democratic union would discuss kohls proposal at a 
special committee meeting next week 
everyone knows whoever keeps the border question open closes 
the door on german unity genscher was quoted as saying by the 
newspaper 
other members of the liberal free democrats were even more blunt 
party chairman otto graf lambsdorff said he was in no way 
happy with kohls offer he said he was surprised that the very 
delicate topic of reparations should be mentioned by our side 
