territory but he insists only a future united german government 
can sign a binding agreement facing close races in december 
elections kohl has tried to woo a rightwing minority of voters 
who want to lay claim to the land 
in fridays statement he again avoided stating outright that a 
united germany would not claim the land which makes up about a 
third of poland 
