<TEXT>
thousands of workers at some of hawaiis biggest 
hotels walked off the job saturday leaving some guests without 
fresh sheets and towels and otherwise disrupting the states 
6billionayear tourist industry 
the strike was called about 330 am by local 5 of the hotel 
employees and restaurant employees union which has 7500 members 
said spokesman rod rodriguez the unions membership had voted to 
authorize a strike by a 97 percent margin earlier in the week in 
the dispute over pay and benefits 
the strike affected 11 hotels that account for one of every five 
hotel rooms in hawaii and two of every five hotel rooms in waikiki 
the states main tourist destination 
many hotels were forced to cut back on meal and room services as 
managers scrambled to take the places of the strikers 
most of the hotels that were struck closed their restaurants and 
snack shops and the hotel restaurants that remained open had 
buffet service rather than waiting on tables there are many 
restaurants unaffected by the strike in walking distance of waikiki 
hotels 
maid service was cut severely many guests didnt get fresh 
sheets or towels unless they asked and those who did get maid 
service waited for hours 
its unfortunate considering what im paying for a room 
said jennie peters of huntington hills mich were not thinking 
of leaving though 
union and management leaders couldnt agree even on what the 
last contract offer contained 
bill crawford executive director of the council of hawaii 
hotels said the union rejected a fouryear deal that called for 
annual wage increases of 5 percent plus hikes in benefits that 
boosted the total package to around 7 percent a year 
rodriguez said the union calculated the management proposal at 
around 4 percent which he said was lower than the 5 percent 
package offered friday 
management seems to be going backwards he said the offer 
is meager and measly and shows they could really care less about 
the hotel workers 
crawford called the unions calculations voodoo economics 
he urged hotel workers to return to work 
the union is making a grave mistake he said nobody likes 
a strike but the hotels had to stand firm against totally 
unrealistic union demands that ultimately could hurt the employees 
themselves 
one management employee at the hilton hawaiian village in 
waikiki forced to work a parking booth said he didnt understand 
what the workers were striking for 
i cant believe they want a raise for this job said merv 
ching manager of the resorts valet parking system if anything 
they should get a pay cut 
guests were mixed in their views 
im a union man and i dont feel comfortable staying here 
said gary flintoff a member of painters local 64 in tacoma wash 
weve thought about going to another hotel 
tour bus operators both union and nonunion refused to enter 
enter resort property to pick up passengers in a show of support 
for the strikers tourists using those buses were forced to walk to 
hotels main entrances to board on public streets 
rodriguez said the union proposed a threeyear package that 
called for annual wages increases of 8 percent and total economic 
benefits that would boost the proposal to 10 percent a year in 
return the union would drop its demand for a 5 percent room 
surcharge and a 15 percent food and beverage surcharge that hotel 
workers would share 
management rejected the offer saying it would make their hotels 
uncompetitive 
its unreal and out of context with reality said crawford 
the strike followed a holiday taken friday by workers in 
what the union said was a goodfaith effort to try to reach an 
agreement rodriguez claimed management failed to negotiate with 
the intent of reaching a settlement and said the union would 
remain on strike until a substantial offer was made 
theres got to be something to talk about he said we are 
calling their bluff 
the hotels remained open and were being staffed by management 
there was no word if the individual hotels affected would offer 
discounts 
the affected hotels in waikiki were hilton hawaiian village 
2523 rooms sheraton waikiki 1900 rooms hyatt regency waikiki 
1230 rooms princess kalulani 1150 rooms ilikai hotel 800 
rooms sheraton moana surfrider 793 rooms royal hawaiian hotel 
526 rooms and the kahala hilton 369 rooms 
neighbor island hotels affected included the kona hilton on 
hawaii island 445 rooms sheraton kauai 456 rooms and sheraton 
maui 495 rooms 
