sun 
in 1986 when the sol had fallen to 14000 to the dollar the 
government lopped off three zeros and renamed it the inti sun in 
quechua the indian language spoken by nearly half the population 
four years later a dollar buys 14000 intis which means it 
would buy 14 million soles if they were still around 
