night games for a reported 450 million bornstein said 
its an important part of our programming menu he said 
abc refused to make any of its executives available friday to 
discuss how it intends to pay for the sharp increase in the 
football contract 
but lisa donneson media analyst for county natwest usa said 
she figures abc will lose about 7 million during the first year of 
the new monday night contract make a small profit the second year 
and larger profits in the teens and 20s in the last two years 
her estimates assume a singledigit ad rate increase each year 
and higher rates for ads in the new playoff games she noted the 
networks also may add commercial time to their broadcasts to 
generate more revenue 
some analysts said abc could ill afford to lose monday night 
football particularly because cbs outbid it last year for the new 
major league baseball contract 
banks said the broadcasts also give abc an extra way to promote 
other primetime shows as the network tries to overtake the 
primetime ratings leader nbc 
there is a belief that live sports is still very viable 
programming entity that creates a point of difference that nobody 
can copy banks said 
but he noted that with sports proliferating across the 
channel its continued power to draw crowds and willing 
advertisers will be sorely tested 
